x4freetext: -TOTAL CROSS SECTION OF CADMIUM FOR NEUTRONS OF
2. CADMIUM METAL PLATES OF 99.9 PERCENT PURITY AND
.DUMMY SAMPLES USED TO CORRECT FOR THE SULPHUR
POWDER CONTENT OF THE FIRST SET OF SAMPLES.
.CORRECTION FOR THE SULPHUR IN THE CD-S TAKING
ITS CROSS-SECTION TO BE 1.25 B AT 0.178 EV FROM
.TIME DEPENDENT BACKGROUND DETERMINED BY A METHOD
SIMILAR TO THAT OF SIMPSON ET AL,NUCL.INSTR.METH.,
1.65 PERCENT ERROR IN THE FLIGHT PATH LENGTH GIVING
A 3.3 PERCENT ERROR IN THE ENERGY,
1.4 MICROSECOND ERROR IN COUNTER TIME JITTER GIVING
0.5 MICROSECOND ERROR IN ANALYSER START TIME GIVING
AN ERROR OF 0.9*SQRT(E) IN THE ENERGY,
ERROR OF LESS THAN 0.005 PERCENT IN THE ANALYSER
FREQUENCY CONTRIBUTING LESS THAN 0.01 PERCENT TO THE
LESS THAN 2 PERCENT ERROR IN THE ABSORBER THICKNESS
CONTRIBUTING THE SAME TO THE TOTAL CROSS-SECTION,
1 PERCENT STATISTICAL ERROR GIVING 1.4 PERCENT CROSS-
DEAD TIME ERROR OF LESS THAN 0.2 PERCENT,
ERROR DUE TO IMPURITIES AND CONTENT OF S IN CD-S OF
ERROR DUE TO EFFECT OF GRAIN SIZE IN POWDER SAMPLES
AND INHOMOGENEITY OF LESS THAN 1 PERCENT,
-TOTAL UNCERTAINTY IN A SINGLE MEASUREMENT ESTIMATED
